            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "\nI work in edtech for last 14 years any parent concern are usually prioritize or staff at least tries to acknowledge.\nHsV global director Ms. Chitwan is one such lady who is highly immature and improfessional handling a post of director. I had a concern regarding a shade where parents and kids get traumatized in extreme temperature. While I raise teachers completely ignored and at the reception when I raised director said it's not possible while tried explaining, she asked me to issue a TC.\nI don't understandhow can a director behave like this and what my child is going to learn.\nDaksh teacher collected Taekwondo fee and never reverted on calls. I did raise to Principal Anjali. It wasn't heard.\nThere staff changes regularly but there has been no update...\nI mean how can they run a setup so unprofessionally.\nVery disappointed.\nMy child carries a bag of 10 kg's minimum and has a overall 25kg of body weight.\nI don't know what's wrong initially staff was good but after the director started taking over she has spoiled school goodwill.",
